1.Installation Of Git.
	- Git is the interface tool , used to interact with the GitHub.

	website : https://git-scm.com/downloads
	file name : Git-2.13.2-64-bit.exe

2. create the repository locally.

	- create the folder.
	Ex.

		E:/githubdemo

	- open the GitBash Here terminal
	
	- execute the following command.

	>git init

	[Note : Automatically githubdemo converted as local repository]


3. Add the user credentials to the Repository.

>git config --global user.name "NareshIT"   // add the user name
>git config --global user.email "hr@nareshit.in"  // add the email


4. create the files to the repository
>touch sample.js

Knowing the status of files in Repository
-----------------------------------------
>git status

[Note : "red color label" files indicating untracked files in repository]


5. commit the files to repository

>git add sample.js

>git commit

>press "i"

>type "initial commit"

>press "ESC"

>type ":wq"

>press Enter.

from the 2nd commit onwards:

>git add sample.js
>git commit -m "JavaScript Code Added"

knowing the commit log
----------------------
>git log


6. creating the branch
>git branch "AngularJS_7AM"


7. checkout the branch
>git checkout AngularJS_7AM


8.Merging the Branches to the Master.
>git merge AngularJS_7AM 



9. Integration Of GitHub to the IDE

	IDE - Integrated Development Environment
	- in general the recomended IDE for UI Application Development is WebStrom.


Download and install the NodeJS
--------------------------------

website : https://nodejs.org/en/download/

file name : node-v6.11.1-x64.

Download and install the IDE (WebStrom)
---------------------------------------

Website : https://www.jetbrains.com/webstorm/download/#section=windows

File name : Webstrom-2017.2.exe

Checkout the Code from Cloud Repository
---------------------------------------

URL : https://github.com/ajsnaresh/AJS_Classes.git
Branch : AngularJS_7AM


10. push the code to the cloud repository.


   in webstrom IDE :

            - ctrl+k
            - enter the commit message
            - commit & push
            - push


11. Pull the Code from Repository.

    VCS   --->   Git  ---> Pull ---> AngularJS_7AM ---> Pull.




































































































































